vampire.editor.plugin.api.domain.sheet

Interface MetaAPI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Nameable, PseudoDataAPI<MetaEntryAPI>

    public interface MetaAPI
extends PseudoDataAPI<MetaEntryAPI>
    The MetaAPI is an interface specializing the DataAPI interface.
    It provides an Iterator to get its attached MetaEntries (MetaEntryAPI).

    Implementation Note:
    This interface does not extend the DataAPI interface itself, due to problems with Java Generics.
    But all classes implementing this interface, must also implement the DataAPI interface.
    Nevertheless this interface demands all methods demanded by DataAPI.
    Author:
    rex_victor
